Usage: addAIoFiller [-help] [-onlyESD] [-onlyGap] [-onlyShoulder]
                    [-powerDomain <powerDomainName>] [-prefix <prefix>]
                    [-setPreplaced] {-cell <fillerCellName> | -cellList {fillerCellName1 fillerCellName2 ...}} [-allAIORowCluster  | -aioRowCluster <aioRowClusterName>]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-aioRowCluster <aioRowClusterName>     # pecifies the area I/O row cluster name
                                       # to add I/O fillers (string, optional)
-allAIORowCluster                      # adds AIOFiller cells to all the area
                                       # I/O clusters (bool, optional)
-cell <fillerCellName>                 # specifies the name of the area I/O
                                       # filler cell to be added
                                       # (string, required)
-cellList {fillerCellName1 fillerCellName2 ...}
                                       # specifies the list of area I/O filler
                                       # cells (string, required)
-onlyESD                               # only adds ESD cells (bool, optional)
-onlyGap                               # fills all the gaps in the area I/O row
                                       # clusters (bool, optional)
-onlyShoulder                          # only adds shoulder cells
                                       # (bool, optional)
-powerDomain <powerDomainName>         # Specifies the power domain to add area
                                       # I/O filler cells (string, optional)
-prefix <prefix>                       # specifies the prefix of the area I/O
                                       # filler cell instance (string, optional)
-setPreplaced                          # sets the status of the area I/O filler
                                       # cells as preplaced (bool, optional)